    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to drawings that are made using three-point perspective, which is either a system of linear perspective using three vanishing points where rectangular objects are set at an angle to the picture plane or a depiction where there are three points of view.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a dibujos que son realizados usando la perspectiva de tres puntos, que corresponde tanto a un sistema de perspectiva linear usando tres puntos de fuga en donde objetos rectangulares son puestos en un ángulo al plano de la imagen o una representación en donde hay tres puntos de vista.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar tekeningen die zijn gemaakt vanuit het drie-puntsperspectief, een lineair perspectief met drie verdwijnpunten waarbij rechthoekige objecten in een hoek ten opzichte van het beeldvlak zijn weergegeven, of een afbeelding waarbij sprake is van drie gezichtspunten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052399/Nederlandse Film en televisieacademie</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指運用三點透視法製作的圖則，即運用三個消失點的線性透視系統，其長方形物件與繪畫平面成特定角度。該詞彙亦指具有三個視點的描繪。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se aos desenhos que são feitos usando perspectiva de três pontos - isto é, um sistema de perspectiva linear com três pontos de fuga no qual objetos retangulares são colocados em um ângulo no plano da imagem - ou à uma representação na qual há três pontos de vista.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
